# Provenance for boot-log.golden — captured 2026-07-06.
#
# World data source: https://github.com/Noobinabox/RotS-WorldFiles (see CLAUDE.md
# "World files and player data are not in this repo"). The local lib/world/
# checkout used to capture this golden has no .git/ (imported as a plain
# snapshot, not a clone), so there is no commit hash to pin — instead we record
# a file-count + byte-size fingerprint of lib/world/ at capture time:
#
#   files: 1887
#   bytes: 25290200
#
# Regenerate this golden (scripts/boot-golden.sh capture) whenever lib/world/
# changes — a different world snapshot will boot-load different
# zones/mobs/objects and legitimately shift the normalized boot log.
#
# --- Recaptured 2026-07-10 (Phase 4 Wave 2, Task 1) ---
#
# INTENTIONAL, user-approved (sign-off 2026-07-10) behavior change: zone.cpp's
# load_zones() read the 8 always/conditionally-present reset_com fields
# (if_flag/arg1..arg7 -- all declared `int` in db.h) with fscanf("%hd", ...),
# writing through each `int*` as if it pointed at a `short` -- undefined
# behavior that, on this little-endian target, silently truncated any
# negative or >32767-magnitude argument to its low 16 bits embedded in an
# otherwise-zeroed int. Fixed to %d (matching the declared field type and the
# already-%d write side in shapezon.cpp); see zone_tests.cpp
# (ZoneLoad.NegativeOneArgumentParsesAsSignedNegativeOne) for the pinned unit
# regression and the Task 1 report (.superpowers/sdd/w2-task-1-report.md) for
# the full before/after boot-log diff, per-line root cause, and the census of
# every affected .zon command argument (both the literal "-1" sentinels the
# task scoped for, and a handful of other negative world-data values that hit
# the identical bug).
#
# lib/world/ is BYTE-FOR-BYTE UNCHANGED across this recapture (still files:
# 1887, bytes: 25290200 -- confirmed identical to the fingerprint above) --
# every line that changed in this golden is attributable to the code fix, not
# to a world-data update.
